The paper deals with decision-making for automated vehicles in complex driving environments, which is a problem in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed framework incorporates uncertainties and uses expert knowledge to guide branching, which involves machine learning (cs.AI) and decision trees (cs.LG). The framework also involves control systems (cs.SY) and perception (cs.CV) to handle perception uncertainties.
